Currently, only users with system administration privileges may import a workflow.  This makes sense for importing a workflow from a file on the filesystem, but doesn't make sense for importing a workflow that has been pasted into the text area on the workflow import screen.  The inability for a regular administrator to import a workflow increases the load on JIRA Studio support, as customers do not have system administration privileges on the JIRA instance.  It would be a great improvement if regular administrators were permitted to import a workflow by pasting in the XML of the workflow, while still restricting them from importing one from the filesystem.

