The jira.issue.editable workflow property is used by SimpleWorflowManager to test whether the issue should be accessible for editing by any user. The test does not trim whitespace characters out of the property value, so that e.g. a value 'false ' would still cause the issue to be available for editing. This has already caused issues with some of JIRA users.

SimpleWorkflowManager#isEditable:
{code}
public boolean isEditable(Issue issue)
    {
        ...
                if (!"false".equals(currentStep.getMetaAttributes().get(JiraWorkflow.JIRA_META_ATTRIBUTE_EDIT_ALLOWED)))
               {
                     return true;
               }
       ...
    }
{code}

